# {{ bundle }}

## Installation

### Get the bundle using composer

Add {{ bundle }} by running this command from the terminal at the root of
your symfony project:

```bash
composer require {{ vendor_name_lower }}/ez-{{ bundle_short_lower }}-bundle
```

## Enable the bundle

To start using the bundle, register the bundle in your application's kernel class:

```php
// app/AppKernel.php
public function registerBundles()
{
    $bundles = array(
        // ...
        new {{ namespace }}Bundle\{{ bundle }}(),
        // ...
    );
}
```

## Add routing

Add to your global configuration app/config/routing.yml

```yaml
{{ vendor_name_lower }}.{{ bundle_short_lower }}:
    resource: '@{{ bundle }}/Resources/config/routing.yml'
{% if platform_ui %}
    defaults:
        siteaccess_group_whitelist: 'admin_group'
{% endif %}
```
